    &quot;text&quot;: {
      &quot;primary&quot;: {
        &quot;$type&quot;: &quot;color&quot;,
        &quot;$value&quot;: {
          &quot;light&quot;: &quot;{color.gray.900}&quot;,
          &quot;dark&quot;: &quot;{color.gray.900}&quot;
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

When resolving light mode: color.text.primary → {color.gray.900} → resolve light mode → #1a1a1a
Mode inheritance
Groups can define mode strategy that applies to nested variables.
Example:
{
  &quot;color&quot;: {
    &quot;$extensions&quot;: {
      &quot;modes&quot;: [&quot;light&quot;, &quot;dark&quot;]
